sp.p:
I can't help that—can I ? But I shan't be in a hurry; I shall do as you do—look about me ;
    perhaps somebody may offer that I should like better. (clock strikes) Hark!
    that's two o'clock!—and I promised to meet the captain at the sun-dial yonder. Good bye, Peter;
    and mind, if you can find me a husband that I should like better than any of these, I'll make
    you a present the day I'm married, and you shall dance at the wedding!
